    {
      "id": "R193JQEY0K71F6",
      "title": "Proven ineffective — does NOT remove chlorine (verified against RO system) — do NOT use for babies",
      "body": "Proven ineffective — does NOT remove chlorine (verified against RO system) — do NOT use for babiesI am writing this because people, especially parents, deserve accurate information.This product claims to remove “harsh chemicals” like chlorine. I tested that claim directly using multi-parameter water test strips.I tested:• Unfiltered tap water• Filtered water at normal flow• Filtered water after proper activation (2–3 minutes hot water as instructed)• Filtered water at very slow flow to increase contact timeMost importantly, I also tested water from a reverse osmosis (RO) system as a control. The RO water showed zero chlorine, confirming that the test strips and method are working correctly.Across every test condition, the results were the same:• Tap water chlorine: approximately 0.5–1 ppm• Filtered water chlorine: approximately 0.5–1 ppmThere was no meaningful reduction in chlorine.At the same time, total dissolved solids (PPM) increased after filtration, meaning the water contained more dissolved material after passing through the unit.Based on direct testing, this product does not remove chlorine and does not meaningfully improve the water quality in that regard. The comparison with the RO system makes this clear, as the RO water showed zero chlorine while this product showed no change.Final verdict:• Does not perform as advertised• Does not remove chlorine• Increases dissolved solids• Fails under controlled testingIf you are buying this to make bath water safer for your baby, do not rely on this product. It does not do what it claims.",
